remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a5929-102">Normalisation de reconnaissance vocale est l’utilisation des constructions particulières ou des symboles pour exprimer la reconnaissance vocale dans l’écriture.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-102">Speech normalization is the use of special constructs or symbols to express speech in writing.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a5929-103">Par exemple, supposons qu’il s’agit de texte reconnu :</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-103">For example, suppose that this is recognized text:</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a5929-104">« juillet quatre à douze trente un PM, j’acheté kg d’un point de six de poisson quatorze dollars et six cents, à la pike place de marché de seattle washington neuf huit un deux deux »</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-104">"july four at twelve thirty one PM, I bought one point six kilograms of fish for fourteen dollars and six cents, at the pike place market in seattle washington nine eight one two two"</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a5929-105">Il s’agit du même texte après la normalisation :</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-105">This is the same text after normalization:</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a5929-106">« Le 4 juillet à 12:31 PM, j’ai acheté 1,6 kg de poisson pour $14.06, à la pike place de marché dans Seattle WA 98122 »</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-106">"July 4 at 12:31 PM, I bought 1.6 kg of fish for $14.06, at the pike place market in Seattle WA 98122"</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a5929-107">Dans cet exemple, il existe cinq substitutions, chacun d’eux est décrit par une instance de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-107">In this example there are five substitutions, each of which would be described by an instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a5929-108">À l’aide de la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> de l’objet, une application peut déterminer :</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-108">Using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> object, an application can determine:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="a5929-109">L’emplacement et le nombre de mots remplacé par la normalisation.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-109">The location and number of words replaced by normalization.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a5929-110">Pour plus d'informations, consultez <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.FirstWordIndex%2A> ou <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.CountOfWords%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-110">For more information, see <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.FirstWordIndex%2A> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.CountOfWords%2A>.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="a5929-111">Le texte remplacé et ses attributs d’affichage.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-111">The replaced text and its display attributes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a5929-112">Pour plus d’informations, consultez <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.Text%2A>, et <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.DisplayAttributes%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-112">For more information, see <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.Text%2A>, and  <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.DisplayAttributes%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a5929-113">Instances de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> sont généralement fournies en tant que membres de la <xref:System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection%601> objet retourné par la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.ReplacementWordUnits%2A> propriété sur <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> (ou les classes qui héritent de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>, tel que <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>) lorsque le texte retourné a été normalisé.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-113">Instances of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> are typically obtained as members of the <xref:System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection%601> object returned by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.ReplacementWordUnits%2A> property on <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> (or classes that inherit from <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>, such as <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>) when returned text has been normalized.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a5929-114">L’exemple ci-dessous affiche des informations dans une interface utilisateur sur un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> objet retourné par un moteur de reconnaissance.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a5929-114">The example below displays information in a user interface about a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> object returned by a recognition engine.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
internal static void DisplayBasicPhraseInfo(  
        Label label,   
        RecognizedPhrase result,   
        SpeechRecognizer rec)   
{  
  if (result != null && label != null)   
  {  
    // Blank  
    if (rec != null)   
    {   
      // Clear  
      label.Text += String.Format(  
                             "  Recognizer currently at:   {0} mSec\n" +  
                             "  Audio Device currently at: {1} mSec\n",  
                             rec.RecognizerAudioPosition.TotalMilliseconds,  
                             rec.AudioPosition.TotalMilliseconds);  
    }  
  
    if (result != null)   
    { // Clear  
      RecognitionResult recResult = result as RecognitionResult;  
      if (recResult != null)   
      {  
        RecognizedAudio resultAudio = recResult.Audio;  
        if (resultAudio == null)   
        {  
          label.Text += String.Format("  Emulated input\n");  
        }   
        else   
        {  
          label.Text += String.Format(  
                               "  Candidate Phrase at:       {0} mSec\n" +  
                               "  Phrase Length:             {1} mSec\n" +  
                               "  Input State Time:          {2}\n" +  
                               "  Input Format:              {3}\n",  
                               resultAudio.AudioPosition.TotalMilliseconds,  
                               resultAudio.Duration.TotalMilliseconds,  
                               resultAudio.StartTime.ToShortTimeString(),  
                               resultAudio.Format.EncodingFormat.ToString());  
        }  
      }  
  
      label.Text += String.Format("  Confidence Level:          {0}\n", result.Confidence);  
      if (result.Grammar != null)   
      {  
        label.Text += String.Format(  
                            "  Recognizing Grammar:       {0}\n" +  
                            "  Recognizing Rule:          {1}\n",  
                            ((result.Grammar.Name != null) ? (result.Grammar.Name) : "None"),  
                            ((result.Grammar.RuleName != null) ? (result.Grammar.RuleName) : "None"));  
      }  
  
      if  (result.ReplacementWordUnits.Count !=  0)    
      {  
        label.Text += String.Format("  Replacement text:\n");  
        foreach (ReplacementText rep in result.ReplacementWordUnits)    
        {  
          string repText = rep.Text;  
          // Add trailing spaces  
  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.OneTrailingSpace) !=  0)    
          {  
            repText += " ";  
          }  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.TwoTrailingSpaces) !=  0)    
          {  
            repText += "  ";  
          }  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.ConsumeLeadingSpaces) != 0)    
          {  
            repText=repText.TrimStart();  
          }  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.ZeroTrailingSpaces) != 0)   
          {  
            repText = repText.TrimEnd();  
          }  
          label.Text += String.Format(  
                           "      At index {0} for {1} words. Text: \"{2}\"\n",  
                           rep.FirstWordIndex,  rep.CountOfWords, repText);  
  
        }  
        label.Text += String.Format("\n\n");  
      }  
    }  
  }    
}  
```

  
  
